The paper deals with fault-tolerance and optimization of distributed stream processing systems, which are typically studied in the Distributed, Parallel, and Cluster Computing (cs.DC) sub-category. The paper also involves the analysis of system topology and message delay, which are relevant to the Distributed Systems (cs.DS) sub-category. The paper's focus on fault-tolerance and system optimization also suggests the Systems and Control (cs.SY) sub-category. The paper's use of mathematical modeling and optimization techniques suggests the Probability (cs.PF) sub-category. Finally, the paper's use of Apache Flink, a popular distributed stream processing system, suggests the Networking and Internet Architecture (cs.NI) sub-category.
